    "text": "The local runtime now requires page perception outputs to pass quality gates before downstream modules consume high-signal context.\nResearchers reported that grounded source references reduce false summaries because every claim keeps a fallback quote and content hash.\nThe release defines sourceCoverage, groundingCompleteness, jumpbackCoverage, and noiseRatio as required metrics for automated acceptance.\nTeams can inspect rejected low-signal blocks in debug evidence without exposing extractor-specific candidate output as final contract data.\nThe implementation keeps a DOM baseline path so validation can run on local fixtures without network access or optional third-party extractor packages.\nRelated articles: browser extensions, unrelated product launch, sponsored newsletter\nAdvertisement sponsored by Example Cloud\nFor developers, the key procedure is to validate schema, fixture gates, quality metrics, and boundary checks after every substage.",
